.TH barto-cli 1  "barto-cli 1.4.2" 
.SH NAME
barto\-cli \- Command\-line tool for querying bartos instances
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbarto\-cli\fR [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR]... [\fB\-e\fR|\fB\-\-enable\-std\-output\fR] [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-config\-absolute\-path\fR] [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-tracing\-absolute\-path\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Command\-line tool for querying bartos instances
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Turn up logging verbosity (multiple will turn it up more)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Turn down logging verbosity (multiple will turn it down more)
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-enable\-std\-output\fR
Enable logging to stdout/stderr
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\-absolute\-path\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Specify the absolute path to the config file
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-tracing\-absolute\-path\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Specify the absolute path to the tracing output file
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
barto\-cli\-secrets(1)
Manage barto secrets in the platform keychain (no bartos connection needed)
.TP
barto\-cli\-info(1)
Display the bartos version information
.TP
barto\-cli\-updates(1)
Check for recent updates on a bartoc client
.TP
barto\-cli\-cleanup(1)
Perform cleanup of old database entries
.TP
barto\-cli\-clients(1)
List the currently connected clients
.TP
barto\-cli\-query(1)
Run a query on bartos
.TP
barto\-cli\-list(1)
List the output for the given command
.TP
barto\-cli\-failed(1)
List the jobs that failed
.TP
barto\-cli\-cmd(1)
Display output for the given command name across all clients
.TP
barto\-cli\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v1.4.2
